.TH BUNPY-VERSION 1 "2026-04-27" "bunpy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bunpy-version \- print build metadata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bunpy version
[\fB\-\-short\fR | \fB\-\-json\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints the version, build commit, build date, host go/os/arch,
and the three pinned sibling-toolchain commits (gopapy, gocopy,
goipy) baked into the binary at build time.
.PP
A locally-built binary prints just
.B bunpy dev
followed by the go/os/arch line. Release builds add the commit,
build date, and toolchain pins so a release archive is
self-describing.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-short
Print just the version string. Useful in shell pipelines.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Print the metadata as a one-line JSON object. Empty fields are
omitted. Keys:
.IR version ", " commit ", " build_date ", " goipy ", " gocopy ", " gopapy ", " go ", " os ", " arch .
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ bunpy version --short
0.0.7
$ bunpy version --json | jq .commit
"abcdef0"
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bunpy (1).
